17/07/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg officially announced personnel changes in his cabinet Wednesday (16 July).
The reshuffle includes the dismissal of four ministers:
transport and communications, health, education and the minister without portfolio.
Economy Minister Nikolay Vassilev will now move to the transport ministry, and will be replaced by current Labour and Social Policy Minister Lidia Shuleva.
Parliament will debate the changes Thursday.
In other news, the European Commission is recommending that the Council of Ministers close the justice chapter in accession talks with Bulgaria.
Sofia reportedly has expressed a strong commitment to implement necessary reforms in this area.
(Dnevnik, Sega, Pari, Trud, 24 Chassa - 17/07/03;
BTA, BNT, Nova TV - 16/07/03)
